[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man, 21, dies after car crash on the M74

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 21-year-old man has died following a road crash on the M74 near Bothwell.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
He was driving a blue coloured Ford Fiesta southbound near the Raith Interchange when it happened at 23:05 on Saturday.
Police said the car apparently went out of control causing it to cross the central reservation, hit a lamppost and overturn before coming to rest on the opposite carriageway.
The man was taken to Monklands Hospital where he died a short time later.
